### Phase 8B — Repair `containers/environment.yml` (delegated to junior bioinformatician)

> **Why**: The original `environment.yml` was syntactically valid but
> semantically unresolvable. The pins (`r-cicero 1.3`, `r-seuratdisk
> 0.0.9021`, `r-seuratwrappers`, `celloracle`, `gimmemotifs`) referenced
> packages that are not in conda-forge/bioconda anymore or that were never
> published there. The `docker build` command has been failing on this
> project since before Phase 0.

> **How**: Detailed instructions are in the chat with the user; the
> deliverable is a working `containers/environment.yml` that produces
> `mamba env create -f containers/environment.yml` exit 0.

- [ ] **8B.1** Audit each pinned version against anaconda.org / bioconda
      channel state (October 2025 - June 2026).
- [ ] **8B.2** Replace `r-cicero 1.3` with a `BiocManager::install("cicero")`
      call in a `RUN` step in the Dockerfile (cicero is Bioconductor-only).
- [ ] **8B.3** Pin `r-seuratdisk=0.0.9019` (latest available on conda-forge).
- [ ] **8B.4** Remove `r-seuratwrappers` (it is now bundled in Seurat v5+).
- [ ] **8B.5** Move `celloracle`, `gimmemotifs`, `goatools`, `adjustText`
      to the `pip:` section of `environment.yml`.
- [ ] **8B.6** Bump `r-base` from 4.3 to 4.4 to match the r44 build-string
      that conda-forge currently ships for r-seurat/r-signac.
- [ ] **8B.7** Add `bioconductor-biocmanager` and `r-remotes` so the
      Dockerfile can install cicero in a post-conda step.
- [ ] **8B.8** Validate with `mamba env create -n test -f containers/
      environment.yml` (no Docker required).
- [ ] **8B.9** Validate the full Docker build with `docker build -t
      scmultiome-grn:dev -f containers/Dockerfile containers/`.
- [ ] **8B.10** Smoke-test inside the container: `docker run --rm
      scmultiome-grn:dev Rscript -e 'library(Seurat); library(Signac);
      library(cicero); library(EnsDb.Mmusculus.v79)'`.

