      `nextflow run main.nf -profile test --percentile 95 -resume` — both
      must complete and the cache behaviour must remain identical.

### Phase 8G — Cache CellOracle motifs (optional but recommended)

> **Why**: `AGENTS.md` warns that CellOracle downloads TF motif databases
> on first run. If the venue Wi-Fi fails during the live demo, the
> pipeline crashes. Pre-caching the motif DB eliminates that risk.

> **How**:

- [ ] **8G.1** Run CellOracle once locally with internet access and let
      it download the default motif DB (`gimme.vertebrate.v5.0`,
      ~ 500 MB) to `~/.celloracle/` or wherever CellOracle caches it.
- [ ] **8G.2** `tar czf assets/celloracle_motif_cache_vX.Y.Z.tar.gz
      ~/.celloracle/` and commit the archive to the repo (it's
      reproducible content, < 500 MB).
- [ ] **8G.3** Modify `bin/GRN_analysis.py` to honour a
      `MOTIF_CACHE_DIR` env var and unpack the cache to that path before
      the first CellOracle call.
- [ ] **8G.4** Document the cache in `data_demo/README.md` and
      `docs/usage.md`.

### Phase 8H — Add a dataset overview plot generator (optional, high wow-factor)

> **Why**: For the live demo, a UMAP coloured by CellType and a volcano
> plot of DE genes Homeostatic vs LateDAM give the audience a
> "preview" of the dataset before the pipeline runs. This is the moment
> the audience goes from "abstract bioinformatics" to "ah, I see the
> microglia turning on Trem2 and Apoe".

> **How**:

- [ ] **8H.1** Create `data_demo/plot_dataset_overview.py` that loads
      the `.h5ad` and produces:
      - `overview_umap.png` — UMAP coloured by `CellType`.
      - `overview_volcano.png` — Volcano of
        `Microglia_Homeostatic` vs `Microglia_LateDAM` with
        `{Apoe, Trem2, Tmem119, Hexb, C1qa, Csf1r}` highlighted.
      - `overview_marker_heatmap.png` — Heatmap of the 4 canonical
        markers per CellType.
- [ ] **8H.2** Add an `--overview` flag to `subsample_dataset.py` that
      runs the plot script after writing the `.h5ad`.
- [ ] **8H.3** The plots land in `data_demo/processed/` and are
      committed as part of the demo deliverable.
- [ ] **8H.4** Update `docs/output.md` to reference the new overview
      plots and explain their biological interpretation.

